a little post hot yoga self care was on the menu this evening. my self care needs tend to show up differently for me every day, every week, every month. Zit patches and a workout!!!! 🧖‍♀️🌷☀️💪 I got a gym membership. And I’m fucking thrilled about it. It has been a bit since my body, mind, and life felt solid and aligned to dive into lifting consistently. I’m taking it slowly, listening to how my body wants to show up, and learning where to push in discomfort vs giving myself a break. And damn it feels great to get to know yourself on that level. That shits power!!! So, here’s a workout I did today — a little mix of different body parts. I’m not following a program, I’m not dedicating certain days to certain body parts,… just moving and finding love for that + the mind-body connection again. Maybe some day I’ll get a bit more structured, but this is just feeling so good right now. A reminder to release pressure on yourself and feel through what you need to — that tends to be right when it starts feeling great ❤️

THE WORKOUT ➡️
SET 1
• 10 cable squats 
• 10 cable RDLs 
SET 2
• 12 cable pulls / rows
SET 3
• 12 pause leg press (I’m clearly a fan of the gym consistently playing the chainsmokers lol. Pause at the bottom of the rep! Shit burnssss)
SET 4
• 12 machine pull downs
SET 5
• 15 crunches (this machine was DOPE — but use a cable or just do regular crunches if you don’t have this bad boy)

Enjoy 🤌

it has officially been a month since moving to san diego. the decision to move here happened quickly yet thoughtfully. I felt so calm and confident in the decision. I was ready for the next chapter of my life on many fronts — location, environment, mental, habits, work, etc. denver served such a beautiful time to me in the 3.5 years I was there. I met wonderful people, I gained incredible work experience, I grew into my self, voice, and confidence more than ever. closing a chapter and diving into one that is completely new and uncharted territory can be nerve wracking. that’s the nature of something new, but that’s also right where absolute magic can reveal itself. if you’re feeling the push or curiosity to do something different, something somewhat scary, something new… and the thought + feeling doesn’t leave you… I encourage you to just step into it and launch yourself into exciting choices. trust your thoughtfulness, trust your intuition, and let yourself live in that newness. it’s where you can find and create parts of yourself, deepen awareness, unveil understanding, and ultimately, define how you show up for yourself.

you know I’m always scheming on how to add @youcanbeam vegan protein to a recipe… beam is queen okay!!!! 👑🍓🍨🍫 this natural vanilla vegan protein is becoming a major fave. so versatile!!! anyway. these absolutely tickle my fancy. I ate them all in less than 12 hours lol. dairy free, high protein, easy to make (although chopping strawberries with nails is always a trip), and refreshingly delicious. 

1️⃣ chop up your strawbs 🍓 I used what I had left of strawberries (about 10), but wish I used a whole carton!!!
2️⃣ mix 1/2 cup - 1 cup yogurt with a scoop of @youcanbeam natural vanilla vegan protein 🍨 (DC “ali” for savings) amount of yogurt depends on how many strawberries you’re using. you want them to be evenly coated.
3️⃣ fold your strawberries into the protein yogurt mixture.
4️⃣ scoop clusters on to parchment paper and freeze for 30+ minutes.
5️⃣ once frozen, prepare your chocolate. melt 1/2 cup - 1 cup of chocolate + 1/2 tablespoon coconut oil. I used a sea salt chocolate (@lilys_sweets) and oh myyyyy the little bit of salt took it next level.
6️⃣ coat your clusters in the chocolate. drizzle over top as needed.
7️⃣ stick em back in the freezer for 10+ minutes.
8️⃣ enjoyyyyyyy and store in the freezer!

#youcanbeam #healthydessert #highproteindessert #healthysnack #vegandessert

+++ here to remind you to embrace your blemishes 🫶 been going thruuu it with a new chapter in the acne journey the past few months and am now beginning to clear some inflamed shit. I’m excited to talk more about it and share what I’ve learned. regardless, it can be hard to show up online or in life when you are experiencing apparent changes on your face. I feel you, I get you. remind yourself that there is so much power within you leaning in — getting to know your skin and inner + outer workings, learning to listen to what your body needs, what your mind needs, being consistent with a routine, acting on how you fuel and care for your body, reflecting on how you best break through moments of insecurity or confusion… it all takes time. but look, you’re practicing some awesome qualities — discipline, learning yourself inside and outside, depending your knowledge around a subject, being curious, lessening judgment, practicing separating your worth from appearance, and finding what makes you, you… it’s tough, but it can be a beyond skin, profound transformative thing. sending love ✨
